  "content": "<p>2\ufe0f\u20e39\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 29th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>Among (many) other things systemd&#39;s service manager is also a resource manager. It can assign CPU, IO, memory resources to services, measure their use, and apply live modifications to it.</p><p>There&#39;s one fundamental type of resource it so far didn&#39;t manage per-service however: disk space. With v258 we are changing that.</p>",
